cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.SD, cs.CC 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it focuses on leveraging social media data to better understand and improve engineering diversity. It could also belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it discusses the social impact of engineering diversity initiatives. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as it uses computational methods to analyze social media data. It may also fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it discusses novel ways of connecting with relevant audiences through social media campaigns. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it discusses the complexity of addressing diversity issues in engineering.
